comments: Avdija (WAS) jumps alongside Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) path and marginal body contact occurs as Gilgeous-Alexander contorts himself around Avdija during the driving shot attempt.
Beal (WAS) establishes himself in Williams' (OKC) path and does not deliver contact.
Dort (OKC) initiates contact with Porzingis' (WAS) arm, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Beal (WAS) and Dort (OKC) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs after the switch on the pick.
Avdija (WAS) is moving alongside Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) path and marginal body contact occurs as they come together during the drive.
Avdija (WAS) adjusts to Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) new path, during the cutback to the basket, and marginal body contact occurs as they come together during the driving shot attempt.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) and Avdija (WAS) simultaneously make clean ball contact during their pursuit of the rebound, and a jump ball is correctly whistled after the clean tie-up.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) is moving alongside Avdija's (WAS) path and marginal body contact occurs as they come together during the drive.
Dort (OKC) contest Avdija's (WAS) shot and marginal lower body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) jumps alongside Avdija's (WAS) trajectory with one forearm collapsed to his body and the other arm vertical as he avoids contact with Avdija's head during his contest.
After the made basket, Avdija (WAS) lands awkwardly and stumbles into his teammate Goodwin (WAS) as incidental lower body contact occurs.
Porzingis (WAS) contests the dunk attempt and marginal follow-through contact occurs with Williams' (OKC) arm after the release.
Dort (OKC) is moving alongside Beal's (WAS) path and marginal body contact occurs as they come together during the drive.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he moves to imminently guard an opponent.
Dort (OKC) contests the layup attempt and marginal contact occurs with Kuzma's (WAS) off-arm after the release.
Beal (WAS) brings his arm toward Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) path and marginal contact occurs as they quickly disengage during the drive.
Morris (WAS) engages with Wiggins (OKC) and incidental foot to foot contact occurs with Williams (OKC) as they all jostle for rebounding position.
Dort (OKC) immediately slides his hand off Porzingis (WAS) and marginal contact occurs as they disengage from the pick.
Beal (WAS) stops his forward momentum and does not extend his forearm as marginal contact occurs when he releases away from Dort (OKC) at the end of the drive.
Dort (OKC) legally contests Beal's (WAS) jump shot attempt.
During the inbound, Morris (WAS) and Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) mutually engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) brings his off-arm toward Morris (WAS) and marginal contact occurs as Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) releases away without applying any force.
Morris (WAS) legally contests Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) jump shot attempt.
During the inbound, Williams (OKC) and Kuzma (WAS) mutually engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Dort (OKC) makes clean contact with the ball and deflects it away from Beal (WAS) prior to incidental contact occurring.

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Beal (WAS) is the last player to touch the ball before it lands out of bounds. Possession is correctly awarded to the Thunder.
